title: For Sale:  IBM 30Cal USGI M1 Carbine
postcontent:
Due to a serious health condition, I am now forced to sell off my personal collection of US Military Firearms.  First up for your consideration is an original WWII era M1 30 Caliber Carbine.  This carbine was produced by International Business Machines (IBM) in November 1943.  IBM produced M1 Carbines for only a 10 month period from August 1943 – May 1944.  There were over 6 million M1 Carbine produced during WWII and IBM only produced around 340,000 making them one of the rarest and sought after manufacturers. 
 This M1 Carbine was purchased from the Civilian Marksmanship Program (CMP).  It is very serviceable with a shiny bore and a muzzle reading of 2.  The barrel is original to the receiver and is stamped “IBM Corp 11-43.”  There are no observed cracks in the stock.  The stock has several markings such as the US Ordnance Wheel (Crossed Cannons), a couple of proof “P” stamps, and “AAA” due to rebuild at Anniston, AL Arsenal.  It is also stamped “FAT” to indicate it was used in Italy at one time in its history.
 $900 Face-To-Face transaction in Jackson, MS area.  I do require a MS Driver License or MS Firearms Permit as identification.  A Bill of Sale will also be issued.

title: For Sale:  458 Socom New
postcontent:
This is a brand new custom built AR15 in the 458 SOCOM caliber.
The upper is an Aero Precision 7075-T6 aluminum forging made specifically for the 458 Socom cartridge.  The upper features a factory oversized ejection port, factory installed dust cover, forward assist, and white “T” marks.  The lower is a matching Aero Precision 7075-T6 aluminum forging marked Multi Caliber.  The lower contains a tensioning screw that can be used to remove all clearance between the upper and lower creating a wobble free assembly.  The adjustable carbine stock, trigger guard, and grip are Magpul MOE in flat dark earth.  The Magpul stock can be adjusted to 6 different positions. The Magpul MOE grip has a storage compartment.  The lower parts kit is Anderson Mfg. milspec.  The aluminum free float hand guard is a 12” long key mod rail system in flat dark earth. The top of the rail is full length picatinny with 2 additional 3” long FDE key mod rails that can be attached anywhere along the sides or bottom of the hand guard.  The ported barrel is manufactured by custom barrel manufacturer Deadshot Barrels.  This 16” barrel is of the heavy contour style and is manufactured from 4140 Chrome Moly steel with a non-reflective black Cerakote coating.  The barrel is ported and therefore does not require a flash hider or muzzle brake.  The ports act as a muzzle brake which keeps the recoil down and since it is integrated into the barrel the overall length is kept to a minimum.  The barrel features a center feed ramp for proper feeding of the 458 SOCOM cartridge.  The barrel is manufactured for a carbine length gas system with a .875” diameter gas block seat.  The underside of the barrel is dimpled for proper gas block alignment.  Rifle comes with one Wilson Combat/Lancer 7 shot magazine specifically made for the 458 Socom cartridge.  Awesome looking and handling rifle.  Nothing to do but mount some optics and start shooting.   Payment:If local cash only.  Must have a CWP or drivers license and sign a bill of sale.  If shipment is required I will only ship to a licensed FFL holder.  Payment can be by USPS money order or certified check.  Shipping within the continental US is $40 and includes insurance.GregREDACTED
